Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into
bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens; mince whites. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}.

== Scallion Rice ==

Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add garlic and half
the @Chili Powder{1%teaspoon} to pot. Cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, half the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2}, 3/4 cup
water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a pinch of @Salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Garlic Lime Broccoli ==

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon},
@Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until
browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Red Pepper Jam Trout ==

Meanwhile, pat @Steelhead Trout{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season
generously with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> Swap in chicken or pork chops for trout. Cook chicken until cooked through,
3-5 minutes per side, or cook pork chops until crispy.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add trout and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} per
side (for thick filet, cook 1-2 minutes more on second side). Transfer trout to
a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add scallion whites and
remaining chili powder; cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Stir in 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), @Red Pepper Jam{1}, and
remaining stock concentrates. Cook, stirring and scraping up any browned bits
from bottom of pan, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} and a squeeze of lime juice.
Season with salt and pepper.

Return trout and any resting juices to pan with sauce; turn a few times to
coat. Transfer trout to a #cutting board{}; slice crosswise.

> No need to slice trout if using whole filet.

Return chicken or pork to pan with sauce; turn a few times to coat. Transfer
chicken or pork to a cutting board; slice crosswise.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Stir in lime zest, half the scallion greens, and a
squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide trout, rice, and broccoli between #plates{}. Spoon remaining pan sauce
over trout and top broccoli with a squeeze of lime juice. Serve.